import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='ignore')
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    ax = sns.lineplot(x='year', y='pop', data=data)
    ax.set(xlabel='Year', ylabel='Population')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('What is the trend of population over time?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):

import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['life_expect'] = pd.to_datetime(data['life_expect'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='ignore')
    ax = sns.histplot(data=data, x='life_expect', kde=True)
    ax.set_xlabel('Life Expectancy')
    ax.set_ylabel('Count')
    ax.xaxis.set_tick_params(rotation=90)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('What is the distribution of life expectancy across countries?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='ignore')
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    ax = sns.barplot(x='cluster', y='fertility', data=data, ci=None)
    ax.set(xlabel='Cluster', ylabel='Fertility Rate')
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('What is the average fertility rate of each cluster?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
